Great food,  good prices, healthy portions, quick & polite service. I walked by today and I had to come in and try some of their food as the aroma was drawing me in. Ordered a large Jerk Pork, white rice with steamed veggies & plantains. Also ordered 4 pieces of fried chicken. Everything was on point and I was impressed with the large portions. Afterwards I was thoroughly full and quite satisfied. I love finding little hole in the wall spots like this, as they are the little culinary gems in the local neighborhoods that make you appreciate well made food. It's a small place without seating but the service was quick and the workers were positive and inviting. I enjoyed my meal right in the park by the Botanical Gardens. Will be back again soon.

We were starving after first Saturday at Brooklyn museum and of course Island had a huge wait so we kept on walking. Eventually we stopped at 3D bakery remembering having some really good beef patties in the past. Of course at around 9pm there were no patties in fact they were just about to close but we convinced the gentleman to give us food. No lie, we pulled him back into the place and he actually agreed (probably seeing our famished slightly tipsy faces) and admitted he only had oxtail and chicken stew. 2 oxtails and 1 chicken stew later... OMG one of the best oxtails I've had. Not to mention the rice & beans being delicious, soft and fresh tasting despite how late it was.  We thanked him and found a stoop to eat our food on. Perfect Saturday night dinner in Brooklyn and I totally recommend this spot- it's affordable and delicious.

This place exactly not a whole in the wall spot but it is close to that category.  We were in the area visiting Brooklyn Museum and decided to grab a bite. Isalnds which nearby was packed(I actually did not have good experience at Islands last time I was there).  While walking we stumbled upon this place, they were ready to close the place. I spoke to the owner he said they some food remaining. I had the curried jerk chicken with rice which comes with salad. My friends had the ribs with rice.  It was about $7-8 bucks for a small size and the small size is actually a lot of food. Our food was delish , so flavorful and tasty. The guy was friendly and nice and accommodated us even when he was about the shop.  Looking  for good and reasonably proved jamaican food then come here.  FYI - They just have 2-3 seats inside so it is mostly a take out spot

This place has got me hooked on their Jamaican beef patties. I was going there and picking up one for a quick lunch/snack ($1.75 each). One day I decided to be adventurous and try their ox tail stew, wow it's great! All their food is pretty affordable and delicious. They also have some good fruit juices there (carrot juice, ginger, and others... they are all packing spices). This is definitely going to be a regular spot for me.
